summary:
Crowley felt dampness suffusing his own shirt. 

This was ridiculous. The last thing he needed now was to be killed. It would...
body:
Crowley felt dampness suffusing his own shirt.
This was ridiculous. The last thing he needed now was to be killed. It would require all sorts of explanations. They didn’t hand out new bodies just like that; they always wanted to know what you’d done with the old one. It was like trying to get a new pen from a particularly bloody-minded stationery department.

- Good Omens by Terry Pratchet & Neil Gaiman

description: Michael Sheen: The story really is about this angel and this demon. A demon who’s not quite as mean and evil as he would like to think he is, and an angel who’s not quite as good as he would like to think he is. I think the more time they spend together the more they start to rub off on each other, I think that says a lot of about us. It’s our flaws and it’s our imperfections that make us who we are.
